&quot;Nnngh.&quot; They had been on the road for hours now, and Ross still hadn't quit his incessant chattering. It was about time he got some sleep.<br>
&quot;Vick, WAKE UP!&quot;<br>
Vick opened his eyes slowly, and suddenly realized he was still holding the wheel. A burst of adrenalin ran through his veins, and he slammed his foot on the brake pedal. &quot;Whoa...&quot;<br>
Ross got out of the car and angrily slammed the door. &quot;Get out. I'm driving now.&quot;<br>
Vick grimaced. &quot;I'm fine. Just need more coffee.&quot; He reached for the cup, but it was empty. &quot;@#%$.&quot;<br>
&quot;Just fine? JUST FINE? Get out of the car and LOOK!&quot;<br>
Ross pointed at the edge of the bridge. They were only a few inches from falling off and careening fifty-five feet into the raging river.<br>
&quot;Whoa.&quot; Vick scratched his head. &quot;I didn't know we were on a bridge.&quot;<br>
Ross opened the driver's side door and was about to get into the car when he heard a strange whooshing noise. &quot;What was that?&quot; he growled.<br>
Vick chuckled. &quot;Sure you don't need a little more sleep there, Ross?&quot;<br>
&quot;Shaddap. I heard something.&quot;<br>
A circular shadow passed overhead, and the whooshing sound caused the bridge to shake.<br>
Vick sat up straight. &quot;I heard that.&quot;<br>
The rumbling continued, and the car began to shake toward the edge of the bridge.<br>
&quot;Get out of the car, NOW!&quot; Ross shouted.<br>
Vick scrambled out as the car teetered over the side of the bridge. Ross opened the trunk and pulled out their field packs, then shuffled a couple yards away from the car. Without warning, another circular shadow passed, and the shockwave was more than enough to shove the car right off the bridge.<br>
Vick barely even heard the splash. Now what are we supposed to do? It's miles from the nearest town... Vick stood and thought. Another rumble and whooshing overhead broke his reverie. Where was it coming from? What were the overhead shadows? Why were they still on the bridge that was wobbling more and more?<br>
