ights are on but nobodys home,'Not completly true i must say,for i am home,i'm just not opening the door. Ah yes,little Lizzy locked away in her room. 'why don't you come outside?its a nice day,' they would say,'no,its going to rain,' i would replay. They would give me a baffled look and walk away.And then,low and behold,it would rain that day! Oh yes,i was right,of course i was.Oh well,that was the past. I look around. Any moment now i expect to wake up,in my warm bed with a cd softly playing in the backround. I always played music during the night,it helped keep nightmares away,as childish as that may sound. I wait for the awakining,but it never comes. Damn.Well,might as well get this thing under way. I look at Anthony expectanly. Mabey he had a clue whats going on,because as sure as hell i didn't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeige.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beige</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 11:34:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/67453 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> The cold wet mushing sounds of Ross's feet were difficult to hear over the pouring rain.<br>
