Win pulled the radio out of his bag, once outside he would have to try to contact control.  He had to warn them.<br>
&quot;Hey Liz, you ok?&quot;  She looked deep in thought, either that or still disgusted by the sweats he gave her.  &quot;Sorry about the smell, I didn't get a chance to wash them after my morning jog...&quot;<br>
Win opened the door, and to no surprise was met with the full blast of the wind.  He had to find a better building, this one was too thick for the radio.  Through the rain he saw the faint flashing lights of a large structure, a radio antenna!<br>
He reached around Liz's shoulders to keep her steady, and also give himself some leverage in the wind.<br>
They came to a large marble building, on the front was a large sign &quot;Waatch, WA Police Department.&quot;<br>
<br>
The inside was desterted, Win's guess was that they must be down in the shelter or out doing their job.  Nontheless, he had to find the room with the CB, he could plug his own radio in there and hopefully get enough juice to reach control.<br>
&quot;Liz, let's split up.  Try to find what looks like a CB radio, call me if you find it.&quot;<br>
He felt bad leaving her alone, but his duties were to his country.  Win looked over as many desks as possible, finally he reached what looked like the Sargent's desk, cluttered on its surface were many reports.<br>
Win picked one up and read it, &quot;Mrs. Sagenti of Waatch reported seeing a circular object pass over her house and make a large rumble.&quot;  Win put it back down and picked up another, &quot;Mr. Robertson of Waatch reported seeing a circular, cigar shaped object pass over his home and leave a supersonic boom.&quot;  Win looked over the other reports, they were ALL UFO sightings! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 1:36:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> The noise was unnerving. Deuce wasn't used to sitting still like this. He wanted a hallway, or a ship deck, or something... something to pace along. He had to move.<br>
<br>
He was going to come unglued.<br>
<br>
The air was alive with electricity... like he was constantly about to be hit by lightening. He wanted to grab something and squeeze the life out of it.<br>
<br>
He had to move.<br>
<br>
Argyle man was starting to stare and make approving looks at him. God how he wanted to shove that guy underwater until he turned blue!<br>
<br>
He had to leave. Get out, some way... or he would end up killing everyone in that room!<br>
<br>
Except maybe swimsuit girl.<br>
<br>
Maybe.<br>
<br>
That hippie shmuck was tossing her some clothing, and waving a cell phone around. Wait. Not a cell phone. It looked like a toy, or something. What the hell were they up to? Did she know him? Deuce didn't think so.<br>
<br>
They're leaving!<br>
<br>
No way!<br>
<br>
Not without Deuce, they weren't!<br>
<br>
He gave them a headstart, then lifted out of his chair. He wound back up the stairs softly, catlike. He heard a rush of wind, and some mist flowed down the stairs and washed his face. <br>
<br>
&quot;Just got dry, too.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce beat tracks up the remaining stairs, and caught the door with his toe. When he stepped out, the wind took part of his breath away.<br>
<br>
He scanned what little he could see through the rain.<br>
<br>
The two had split up! What the hell were they up to? <br>
<br>
And more importantly, who to follow?<br>
<br>
The hippie had some kind of objective... maybe to find a transistor radio or something. But the girl...<br>
<br>
Deuce made his decision, pulled his collar up again, and dove into the rain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeige.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beige</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 3:37:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/67453 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Vick and Ross had been on the road for uncountable hours now. The circular shadows had not abated, although every time Ross seemed to think they would stop, another rumble would pass by and remind him.<br>
&quot;Where the fu..&quot; Ross sneezed. It was fairly certain they had both caught cold, but Vick's frown continued to grow, and he never once coughed, wheezed, sneezed, or done any of the various nasal actions Ross had.<br>
