Ross didn't argue there. They walked down the offramp and spotted a police station nearby. &quot;Ah, that ought to do the trick.&quot;<br>
Vick started running for the station, with Ross huffing and puffing after him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 4:03:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Liz walk through the empty building feeling quite uneasy. The only reassuring thing was her ablility to dart of and disapear. She walked on the toes of her feet,her heels hovering over the ground only and inch or so. <br>
'at least this way,if anything should happen i'll be able to get out of her without to much trouble. Its easier to start running when only have your foot's on the ground,' Liz poked her head inside a room. The room was a bit dark but looked promising so she ventured forth. Ah ah!Against the far wall rested what they had been looking for! Liz tip-toed back to the hallway.<br>
&quot;uh..An-Mr. Meier,'Liz shouted,'i think i found what you were looking for!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeige.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beige</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 4:14:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/67453 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> They arrived at the front doors to the station.<br>
<br>
Ross knocked on the door, but Vick noticed the fact that it was already open. &quot;Dumbass.&quot;<br>
Removing their coats, they ambled on in and looked around. &quot;Where is everybody?&quot;<br>
Vick looked distracted. &quot;There's someone here. I can smell coffee being brewed.&quot; He ran off to find it.<br>
His partner shook his head, and walked after him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/25/01 5:19:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Win heard the voice of Liz over the noise of the rustling papers.  He traced the source and found her in the hallway, both feet on their tip-toes.  She pointed towards a door and he walked in.  There, up against the wall, was the CB Radio they were looking for.<br>
Win gave Liz a cheezy grin, &quot;That's it!&quot;  he pulled out his radio and unplugged his small antenna.  Making sure the two wires were the same size, he plugged his radio into the Police Station's system.<br>
&quot;Control, nine-seven-zero-alpha, do you read?&quot; Win let the button go and listened.  Only static...  Liz gave him a strange smile and rolled her eyes.<br>
&quot;Control, nine-seven-zero-alpha, do you read!&quot; Win let the button go again.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;This is control, what are you doing out in the storm Win?&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Liz gave Winlabik a strange glance.<br>
&quot;It's my codename,&quot; he quickly explained.  &quot;Control, give me a confo on frisbees near Waatch.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;Roger, there are multiple reps of frisbees.  EMF off the charts, advised that you watch the sky if possible, gain evidence.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Win grimmiced.  He hated collecting evidence of UFOs, especially in the midst of a hurricane.<br>
&quot;Roger, Control.  Nine-seven-zero-alpha out.&quot;  Win put down his microphone and disconnected the radio.  Liz stared at him like she thought it was all for nothing.  &quot;They confirmed that UFOs are being sighted all along the Waatch area, and want me to try and get photos.&quot;<br>
Winlabik put his radio into his coat pocket, but noticed two men standing in the doorway of the room.  He was just about to ask them who they were when something loud and fast passed overhead, it left behind a sonic boom that shook the whole building.<br>
All four of them dove for cover under various furniture.  Under the desk Winlabik could only dread if these &quot;visitors&quot; ever went offensive. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 7/25/01 5:19:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/26/01 7:12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> The police station looked like a scaled-down version of every other police station Deuce had visited. Only darker.<br>
<br>
The wind was howling over the roof, and those odd thunderclaps were more incessant.<br>
<br>
But Deuce could still hear every step these people made. His eyes were wide open, his ears pricked, his fingers tingling with electricity. <br>
<br>
The girl found her way into a dark room, and groped around for a bit. Deuce stowed himself in the hallway, keeping an eye on the corners. The hippie was making plenty of noise, so he relaxed a little...<br>
<br>
Until the girl called out for him.<br>
<br>
Deuce sucked in a breath, and tucked into an open doorway before the hippie crossed the hall. Deuce found himself in a small corner office with wide windows taped in large duct tape &quot;X&quot;'s, ready for the worst the storm would give it.<br>
<br>
In the clouds beyond the window, Deuce saw a motion. At first he thought it was a trick of lightening, but then it decended a little and broke through the clouds. Dark, circular... moving really damned fast!<br>
<br>
As it zipped by overhead, it rattled the glass in the windows. That was a familiar sound... a sound from his childhood growing up not far from the Naval base in San Diego.<br>
<br>
What the hell was the military doing sending pilots into the middle of a hurricane?<br>
<br>
A new sound from the hallway caught Deuce's attention. The rickety aluminum door at reception opened with a gust of weather, and two new voices began murmuring.<br>
<br>
Deuce's hand went to his Browning instinctively.  Getting crowded in here!<br>
<br>
He peeled his ears and held his breath. He could hear the hippie droning on into a radio, and was greeted by the static squawk of another voice over the air.<br>
<br>
It was largely jargon... sounded like James Bond wannabees. Maybe a junior Mission Impossible Fan Club.<br>
<br>
But then the hippie said something that made Deuce's eyebrows lift.<br>
<br>
&quot;UFO.&quot;<br>
<br>
Fantastic. A lunatic.<br>
<br>
The newcomers were wandering down the hallway, and the hippie's voice ended upbruptly.<br>
<br>
Deuce relaxed his grip on his piece, and leaned back against the sheetrock, his ear gulping in what it could hear...<br>
<br>
